name: r-googleauthr
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "2.0.0" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-googleauthr
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/googleAuthR_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/googleAuthR/googleAuthR_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: ba504baf3bde2e1b3e988bee7602df5765cc6ca542cf0ab76a782c4e60966feb

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 0
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-assertthat >=0.2.0
    - r-cli >=2.0.2
    - r-digest
    - r-gargle >=0.4.0
    - r-httr >=1.4.0
    - r-jsonlite >=1.6
    - r-memoise >=1.1.0
    - r-rlang
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-assertthat >=0.2.0
    - r-cli >=2.0.2
    - r-digest
    - r-gargle >=0.4.0
    - r-httr >=1.4.0
    - r-jsonlite >=1.6
    - r-memoise >=1.1.0
    - r-rlang

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('googleAuthR')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('googleAuthR')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: http://code.markedmondson.me/googleAuthR/
  license: MIT
  summary: Create R functions that interact with OAuth2 Google APIs  <https://developers.google.com/apis-explorer/> easily, with auto-refresh and Shiny compatibility.
  license_family: MIT
  license_file:
    - {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/MIT
    - LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
